# Content Layer â€” Events and Geological Periods

[`Content.svelte`](src/lib/components/main/content/Content.svelte) renders the foreground timeline content. Viewport pan/zoom and screenâ†’layout coordinate mapping belong in [`Main.svelte`](src/lib/components/main/Main.svelte) â€” see [`main-svelte.mdc`](main-svelte.mdc).

## Layout

- **Geological periods zone** â€” absolute overlay at the top of the content area (above the label band), height `GEOLOGICAL_PERIODS_ZONE_HEIGHT_RATIO` (50%) from [`layout.ts`](src/lib/constants/layout.ts). Renders `GeologicalPeriodCard` items from layouts built by [`geologicalPeriodLayout.ts`](src/lib/utils/geologicalPeriodLayout.ts).
- **Events zone** â€” absolute overlay at the bottom of the content area (above the label band), height `EVENTS_ZONE_HEIGHT_RATIO` (50%) from [`layout.ts`](src/lib/constants/layout.ts). Renders `EventCard` items from layouts built by [`eventLayout.ts`](src/lib/utils/eventLayout.ts).
- **Visibility toggles** â€” `$displaySettings.showEvents` and `$displaySettings.showGeologicalPeriods` from [`displayStore.ts`](src/lib/stores/displayStore.ts) gate each layer independently. Empty/hidden states use locale-aware messages from the `messages` map in `Content.svelte`.
- Data loads on mount from `/events.jsonc` and `/geologicalPeriods.jsonc`.

## Shared span positioning

Horizontal span math lives in [`spanPosition.ts`](src/lib/utils/spanPosition.ts):

- `yearToLayoutX()` â€” maps a year to layout-space X (same axis as timeline ticks)
- `getClampedSpanPosition()` â€” clamped `{ x, width, centerX, startX, endX }` for viewport-visible spans
- `snapLayoutX()` â€” rounds X for crisp 1px markers

Used by geological periods, event layout, and timeline ticks.

Edge-blur span backgrounds use [`spanBandStyle.ts`](src/lib/utils/spanBandStyle.ts) + [`SpanBand.svelte`](src/lib/components/main/content/SpanBand.svelte).

## Event positioning

All event geometry is computed in [`eventLayout.ts`](src/lib/utils/eventLayout.ts) via `buildEventLayouts()` and passed to [`EventCard.svelte`](src/lib/components/main/content/EventCard.svelte) as an `EventLayout` object. Components do not compute their own X/Y.

Date ranges come from [`eventSpan.ts`](src/lib/utils/eventSpan.ts): `date Â± dateUncertainty/2` when uncertainty exists; otherwise a point at `date`.

### Display tiers (zoom-dependent)

| Tier | Condition | Anchor |
|------|-----------|--------|
| `point` | No uncertainty, or span `< 1px` | 1px marker (`w-px`) at `date`, aligned with ticks |
| `range` | `1px â‰¤ span < CARD_WIDTH` | Horizontal bar at zone bottom + center tick at `date` |
| `period` | `span â‰Ą CARD_WIDTH` | Full-height span band with edge fade (`SpanBand`) |

Cards are centered on the best-estimate date with viewport edge clamping (`getEventCardXPosition()`).

### Vertical lane stacking

- Overlap detection uses rendered horizontal footprint: `min(anchor.x, card.x)` to `max(anchor.x + anchor.width, card.x + card.width)`
- Greedy lane assignment sorted by collision left edge
- Default lane step: `EVENT_CARD_HEIGHT + EVENT_LANE_PEEK_GAP_PX` (25px peek)
- Uniform compression when the stack exceeds `eventsZoneHeight`

### Visibility filter

Events are visible when their date range overlaps the viewport (`isEventRangeVisible()`), not when `event.date` alone is in range.

## Geological Period Positioning

- Horizontal span positioning uses `getClampedSpanPosition()` from [`spanPosition.ts`](src/lib/utils/spanPosition.ts); [`geologicalPeriodLayout.ts`](src/lib/utils/geologicalPeriodLayout.ts) exposes `getGeologicalPeriodHorizontalPosition()` as a thin wrapper.
- Vertical geometry (height, bottom offset, z-index by depth) comes from `getGeologicalPeriodCardGeometry()` in [`geologicalPeriodLayout.ts`](src/lib/utils/geologicalPeriodLayout.ts). Child periods occupy `GEOLOGICAL_PERIOD_CHILD_HEIGHT_RATIO` (50%) of the parent height.
- Card backgrounds use per-period `color` from data with neighbor blending via `getSpanBandBackgroundStyle()` in [`spanBandStyle.ts`](src/lib/utils/spanBandStyle.ts). Text uses `var(--theme-on-media)`.
- When selected, a period shows [`GeologicalPeriodPopover.svelte`](src/lib/components/main/content/GeologicalPeriodPopover.svelte) (`data-geological-period-popover`, z-index `1100`) with layout from `getGeologicalPeriodPopoverLayout()`.

## Click-to-Front

- Selection state in `Content.svelte`:
  - `topCardType`: `"event" | "geologicalPeriod" | null`
  - `topCardEventId` / `topCardGeologicalPeriodId` â€” stable ids, not visible index
  - `hoveredCardEventId` + `onCardHover` â€” events only; raises cards temporarily while the pointer is over them
- Z-index tiers on event card and marker:
  - Selected: `1000`
  - Hovered (not selected): `999`
  - Default: `980 + lane`
- Geological period cards use depth-based z-index from `getGeologicalPeriodCardGeometry()` (base `100`, selected `1000`).
- Clicking a card sets selection on `pointerup` via `bindPointerClick` from [`pointerClickOrDrag.ts`](src/lib/utils/pointerClickOrDrag.ts): selection fires only if pointer movement stays below `POINTER_DRAG_THRESHOLD_PX` (5px), otherwise the event bubbles to `Main.svelte` for pan. Do not use `stopPropagation` on card `pointerdown`.
- Deselect via `Main.svelte` `stopDragging`: on a tap (movement â‰¤ `POINTER_DRAG_THRESHOLD_PX`) outside `[data-event-card]`, `[data-geological-period-card]`, and `[data-geological-period-popover]`, call `Content.deselectCards()`. Use the pointerdown target (not pointerup target) because pointer capture retargets events. Do not use per-card `clickOutside` â€” it races with selection.
- Selecting one card type clears the other (`topCardType` enforces mutual exclusivity).

## Styling

- Event cards use theme tokens: `bg-surface-raised`, `border-accent/35`, `ring-accent/30` when selected. Period-tier spans use accent gradient via `SpanBand`.
- Geological period cards use data-driven `color` with CSS gradients; selection adds `border-selection-outline` and scale transform via `getGeologicalPeriodSelectionTransform()`.
- Localize text with `$currentLocale`: event names, descriptions, and dates via `formatDate(event.date, $currentLocale)`; geological period names via `layout.name[$currentLocale]`.

## Performance

- Filter visible events with range overlap via `isEventRangeVisible()` and `$derived` on viewport boundaries.
- Build event layouts with `$derived` via `buildEventLayouts()`.
- Build visible geological period layouts with `$derived` via `buildVisibleGeologicalPeriodLayouts()`.
- Prefer Svelte 5 runes (`$derived`, `$state`, `$props`, `$effect`) over legacy reactive statements.

